LAGOS – In recognition of their performances in the 2019 football year, the trio of Odion Ighalo, Wilfred Ndidi and Victor Osimhen, have made the cut among the nominees for the 2019 Confederation of African Football (CAF) African Footballer of the Year award. The three Nigerians will come up against notable African imports to the world and the list includes holder, Egypt’s Mohammed Salah, and his Liverpool team mate, Sadio Mane from Senegal. There are also Arsenal’s duo of Gabon’s Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang and Cote d’Ivoire’s Nicolas Pepe. Also on the list are Algerian and Manchester City fiery winger, Riyad Mahrez, and Naby Keita of Liverpool and Guinea, among others CAF announced the list of the nominees on Sunday, where Super Falcons and FC Barcelona Ladies’ Asisat Oshoala as well as her national team mate, Goalkeeper Chiamaka Nnadozie, as well as Uchenna Kanu, were among the nominees for the CAF Women Player of the Year. Meanwhile, Osimhen has been nominated for another category, the African Youth Player of the Year, and he is battling Villarreal’s Samuel Chukwueze and 14 other promising African players for the award. Super Eagles’ coach, Gernot Rohr, made the shortlist for African Men’s Coach of the Year, while former Super Falcons coach, Thomas Dennerby, is among the six nominees for African Women’s Coach of the Year. The Super Eagles and Super Falcons have been nominated for the African Men’s National Team of the Year and African Women’s National Team of the Year respectively. The winners of the awards will be announced at the 28th edition of CAF’s annual football awards which will take place on Tuesday, January 7, 2020, at Citadel Azure, Hurghada, Egypt.